Reversing a Customer Queue



A bank in Chennai maintains a queue of customers using a linked list. Due to a system rollback, the bank needs to reverse the order of customers in the queue so that the last customer becomes the first.



Given the head of a singly linked list, reverse the list and print the updated sequence.

Input format :
First line: integer n (number of nodes)
Second line: n space-separated integers (linked list values)
Output format :
First line: reversed linked list (space-separated)
Code constraints :
0 <= n <= 5000
-5000 <= value <= 5000
Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
5
1 2 3 4 5
Output 1 :
5 4 3 2 1
Input 2 :
3
10 20 30
Output 2 :
30 20 10


Solution:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main(){
    
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    
    vector<int>nums(n);
    
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        cin>>nums[i];
    }
    
    reverse(nums.begin(),nums.end());
    
    for(int i:nums){
        cout<<i<<" ";
    }
}
